From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Igor Velkov <iav@iav.lv>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 18:00:00 +0000
Subject: rockchip: rock-pi-4a: cap SPI NOR frequency at 24 MHz

The upstream device tree declares spi-max-frequency = <108000000> for the
SPI NOR on ROCK Pi 4A. On this board that rate is not reliable: the JEDEC
id reads back as ff ff ff and probing fails:

  unrecognized JEDEC id bytes: ff, ff, ff
  Failed to initialize SPI flash at 1:0 (error -2)

The rate cannot be lowered from the U-Boot shell. When the flash node
comes from the device tree, _spi_get_bus_and_cs() calls device_probe() -
and with it the JEDEC id read - while plat->max_hz still holds the value
from spi-max-frequency; the speed passed to `sf probe <bus>:<cs> <speed>`
is only applied further down, after the probe has already failed.

Armbian previously built this board with a downstream patch that declared
the same flash node at 10 MHz, so the chip was detected. That patch targets
the pre-v2026.04 tree and no longer applies once the board follows the
upstream device trees, which is where the 108 MHz value comes from.

Cap the rate in the U-Boot overlay, leaving the upstream device tree
untouched.

Signed-off-by: Igor Velkov <iav@iav.lv>
---
 arch/arm/dts/rk3399-rock-pi-4a-u-boot.dtsi | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/dts/rk3399-rock-pi-4a-u-boot.dtsi b/arch/arm/dts/rk3399-rock-pi-4a-u-boot.dtsi
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/arch/arm/dts/rk3399-rock-pi-4a-u-boot.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/dts/rk3399-rock-pi-4a-u-boot.dtsi
@@ -7,6 +7,7 @@

 &spi1 {
 	flash@0 {
+		spi-max-frequency = <24000000>;
 		bootph-pre-ram;
 		bootph-some-ram;
 	};
